1
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:04,903
PREVIOUSLY ON <i>TATSUKI: TOO KIND FOR SCHOOL</i>

2
00:00:04,904 --> 00:00:06,638
It's pointless if it's not perfect.

3
00:00:06,639 --> 00:00:08,107
Why did you make a mistake?

4
00:00:08,108 --> 00:00:10,042
You want to win the gold medal, right?

5
00:00:10,043 --> 00:00:11,844
<i>I think there's a possibility</i>

6
00:00:11,845 --> 00:00:14,713
that Umine is being subjected
to "tiger parenting."

7
00:00:14,714 --> 00:00:15,681
<i>When I see Umine,</i>

8
00:00:15,682 --> 00:00:17,149
<i>I'm reminded of myself</i>

9
00:00:17,150 --> 00:00:19,184
<i>when I was a child.
So I feel the need to do something.</i>

10
00:00:19,185 --> 00:00:21,320
I understand how you feel,
but you should step back.

11
00:00:21,321 --> 00:00:24,189
Then who is going to
look after her instead?

12
00:00:24,190 --> 00:00:25,858
Who'll listen to her cries for help?

13
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:27,060
Calm down.

14
00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:29,763
Take some time off work.

15
00:00:30,530 --> 00:00:32,532
All I did was hurt you. I'm really sorry.

16
00:00:35,769 --> 00:00:37,002
<i>What's the matter?</i>

17
00:00:37,003 --> 00:00:39,138
She barricaded herself inside.

18
00:00:39,139 --> 00:00:40,272
What?

19
00:00:40,273 --> 00:00:42,342
Umine, come on out.

20
00:00:42,942 --> 00:00:44,177
Call Daddy.

21
00:00:44,844 --> 00:00:45,912
What?

22
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:54,921
Call Tatsuki.

23
00:00:56,156 --> 00:00:57,957
Sorry, I have to go.

24
00:00:59,025 --> 00:01:01,327
- You didn't used to be like this.
- What?

25
00:01:02,695 --> 00:01:04,864
You never helped me when I needed it.

26
00:01:11,137 --> 00:01:12,872
You need to go, right?

27
00:01:21,681 --> 00:01:23,483
Sorry, I'll contact you later.

28
00:01:42,135 --> 00:01:43,069
Tatsuki's here.

29
00:01:43,670 --> 00:01:45,170
- Where've you been?
- Hey there.

30
00:01:45,171 --> 00:01:46,538
- Welcome back.
- Mr. Tatsuki.

31
00:01:46,539 --> 00:01:47,706
Where's Umine?

32
00:01:47,707 --> 00:01:49,175
She locked herself in the room.

33
00:01:55,348 --> 00:01:56,216
Umine.

34
00:01:57,517 --> 00:01:58,351
Sorry.

35
00:02:04,023 --> 00:02:05,225
Can you let me come inside?

36
00:02:31,651 --> 00:02:32,552
What's the matter?

37
00:02:37,423 --> 00:02:39,125
You broke your promise.

38
00:02:41,294 --> 00:02:43,463
You said you'd be by my side
no matter what.

39
00:02:44,397 --> 00:02:46,866
Sorry, I had family matters to attend to.

40
00:02:48,101 --> 00:02:50,603
I was being good, you know.

41
00:02:55,141 --> 00:02:57,176
Want to do something? How about drawing?

42
00:02:57,177 --> 00:02:58,011
No.

43
00:03:00,947 --> 00:03:02,615
I have homework for cram school.

44
00:03:07,654 --> 00:03:08,787
We'll be going now.

45
00:03:08,788 --> 00:03:10,088
- Bye.
- Bye.

46
00:03:10,089 --> 00:03:12,391
- Bye. Stay safe.
- Bye.

47
00:03:12,392 --> 00:03:14,359
- Hello.
- Hello.

48
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,360
Hello.

49
00:03:15,361 --> 00:03:17,095
- Hello.
- Hello.

50
00:03:17,096 --> 00:03:18,297
I'll go call Umine.

51
00:03:18,298 --> 00:03:19,199
Thank you.

52
00:03:21,734 --> 00:03:24,404
Umine, your dad is here.

53
00:03:30,376 --> 00:03:32,645
You can stay longer, if you want.

54
00:03:33,613 --> 00:03:34,447
Mr. Tatsuki.

55
00:03:37,650 --> 00:03:38,718
I'll go.

56
00:03:46,192 --> 00:03:48,661
Do you think Tatsuki is all right?

57
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:52,465
I wonder.

58
00:04:04,210 --> 00:04:05,545
Um…

59
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:09,648
I'll be leaving now.

60
00:04:09,649 --> 00:04:10,683
What will you be…?

61
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:12,751
Oh.

62
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:15,688
I was told to take time off work,

63
00:04:16,889 --> 00:04:18,324
but I have nowhere else to go.

64
00:04:20,493 --> 00:04:21,928
Can I stay here?

65
00:04:24,364 --> 00:04:25,465
I'm sure that's okay.

66
00:04:27,433 --> 00:04:28,401
Sorry.

67
00:04:31,404 --> 00:04:33,773
Then, I'll be going now.

68
00:04:59,432 --> 00:05:01,433
YUKANAI

69
00:05:01,434 --> 00:05:04,337
COUNTERTRANSFERENCE

70
00:05:08,274 --> 00:05:10,710
TATSUKI IS RESTING

71
00:05:14,614 --> 00:05:15,515
Good morning.

72
00:05:16,082 --> 00:05:16,982
Good morning.

73
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:21,220
We have to start getting ready
for the middle school graduation party.

74
00:05:21,788 --> 00:05:22,822
You're right.

75
00:05:23,389 --> 00:05:26,392
This year, Tomoki and Tonetaku
are graduating.

76
00:05:26,959 --> 00:05:28,428
I see.

77
00:05:34,634 --> 00:05:36,234
UMINE

78
00:05:36,235 --> 00:05:38,237
I HAVE TO STUDY AGAIN…

79
00:05:41,140 --> 00:05:45,945
IF YOU CAN'T HANDLE IT…

80
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:49,114
<i>If you lose your head over this,</i>

81
00:05:49,115 --> 00:05:51,217
you won't be able to save her.

82
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:25,317
Kae, you're good at this.

83
00:06:25,318 --> 00:06:26,419
- Really?
- Yeah.

84
00:06:27,286 --> 00:06:29,187
How can I make it into a triangle?

85
00:06:29,188 --> 00:06:32,391
Curve your hand like this,

86
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:33,959
and rotate it like this.

87
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:37,429
But it'll turn into a round ball.

88
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:38,830
No way.

89
00:06:38,831 --> 00:06:40,433
Is Tatsuki not feeling well?

90
00:06:41,601 --> 00:06:43,770
Seems like it. We should let him rest.

91
00:06:44,337 --> 00:06:46,671
I guess I'll be nice
and deliver a rice ball.

92
00:06:46,672 --> 00:06:48,306
Good idea.

93
00:06:48,307 --> 00:06:51,076
I bet Tatsuki is hungry.

94
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:52,677
But isn't the door locked?

95
00:06:52,678 --> 00:06:53,612
TATSUKI IS RESTING

96
00:06:53,613 --> 00:06:54,913
Then…

97
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:56,516
Can Kae and Sakurako take it to him?

98
00:07:01,187 --> 00:07:04,991
Rice balls, rice balls.

99
00:07:07,326 --> 00:07:10,196
Would you like some
freshly made rice balls?

100
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:13,199
Thank you.

101
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:16,202
Tatsuki, are you not feeling well?

102
00:07:18,337 --> 00:07:20,339
Just a little. But no worries.

103
00:07:22,208 --> 00:07:25,477
This one is salted kelp,
but guess what flavor

104
00:07:25,478 --> 00:07:26,512
the other one is.

105
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,714
What could it be?

106
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:30,549
Is it bonito flakes?

107
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:34,587
Eat it and you'll find out.

108
00:07:38,658 --> 00:07:40,226
Okay,

109
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:42,929
then I'll try it.

110
00:07:49,268 --> 00:07:51,337
- How is it?
- Is it good?

111
00:07:52,605 --> 00:07:53,906
It's strawberry!

112
00:07:57,944 --> 00:08:00,279
But it's actually not that bad.

113
00:08:01,347 --> 00:08:03,515
Thank you for your business.

114
00:08:03,516 --> 00:08:04,950
Please excuse us.

115
00:08:04,951 --> 00:08:06,385
Thank you.

116
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,005
- Can I come in?
- Yeah.

117
00:08:29,141 --> 00:08:31,410
I told you to take time off work,

118
00:08:31,944 --> 00:08:33,912
but you don't have
anywhere else to go, huh?

119
00:08:33,913 --> 00:08:35,882
Yeah, sorry.

120
00:08:36,482 --> 00:08:39,719
It seems like Umine will also be taking
some time off for the math competition.

121
00:08:40,453 --> 00:08:41,754
I see.

122
00:08:45,057 --> 00:08:48,060
I wonder if Umine is doing all right.

123
00:08:49,996 --> 00:08:51,163
I wonder.

124
00:09:10,049 --> 00:09:14,253
Why are you so worried about Umine?

125
00:09:18,925 --> 00:09:20,226
I don't know why.

126
00:09:21,527 --> 00:09:24,397
But whenever I see Umine,

127
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:28,568
<i>memories of my own childhood
cross my mind.</i>

128
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:39,345
What is it guys?

129
00:09:42,448 --> 00:09:43,516
All right.

130
00:09:44,016 --> 00:09:45,584
- You guys can come in now.
- Tatsuki.

131
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:48,019
- Tatsuki.
- How are you doing?

132
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:50,189
- Tatsuki, are you all right?
- Yeah, I'm all right.

133
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:53,726
Okay, let's all draw together!

134
00:09:54,293 --> 00:09:56,394
- Yeah!
- Hooray!

135
00:09:56,395 --> 00:09:57,529
What are we drawing?

136
00:09:57,530 --> 00:09:58,530
Anything we want?

137
00:09:58,531 --> 00:09:59,864
Should we use the new paint?

138
00:09:59,865 --> 00:10:01,700
- Good idea.
- Then

139
00:10:01,701 --> 00:10:03,802
let's draw a nostalgic scene
from your childhood.

140
00:10:03,803 --> 00:10:05,037
I'm still a child.

141
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:06,571
You're right.

142
00:10:06,572 --> 00:10:08,874
Then from when you were really little.
Do you remember anything?

143
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:10,776
I have to think about it.

144
00:10:12,345 --> 00:10:13,612
Tatsuki, you should draw too.

145
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:14,512
What?

146
00:10:14,513 --> 00:10:16,782
Scenery I saw when I was little?

147
00:10:18,317 --> 00:10:20,219
Scenery that remains
in your memory even now.

148
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:25,224
Okay.

149
00:10:41,207 --> 00:10:43,542
I'm always impressed
by your drawing skills, Tatsuki.

150
00:10:45,077 --> 00:10:46,579
Were you always good at it?

151
00:10:47,913 --> 00:10:49,215
I'm not sure.

152
00:10:50,249 --> 00:10:52,051
But I always loved to draw.

153
00:11:08,968 --> 00:11:10,136
What's the matter?

154
00:11:10,903 --> 00:11:11,737
It's nothing.

155
00:11:15,474 --> 00:11:18,444
All right, how about we step outside

156
00:11:19,145 --> 00:11:20,312
for a change of pace.

157
00:11:23,883 --> 00:11:25,418
Get in.

158
00:11:26,118 --> 00:11:26,952
Okay.

159
00:11:31,157 --> 00:11:32,691
Where are we going?

160
00:11:32,692 --> 00:11:33,959
I haven't decided.

161
00:11:36,062 --> 00:11:37,596
We'll go where the wind takes us.

162
00:11:40,332 --> 00:11:42,200
So you got to talk with Sora, huh?

163
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:43,035
Yes.

164
00:11:43,803 --> 00:11:47,139
But I've done some pretty awful things…

165
00:11:48,307 --> 00:11:51,143
So when I had to rush back to Yukanai
for Umine,

166
00:11:51,777 --> 00:11:54,046
he told me,
"You didn't used to be like this."

167
00:11:55,981 --> 00:11:59,085
And he said, "You never helped me
when I needed it."

168
00:12:01,587 --> 00:12:03,723
I was at a loss for words.

169
00:12:06,158 --> 00:12:09,260
Well, it looks like it's going to take
a little more time

170
00:12:09,261 --> 00:12:11,130
before your feelings get across to him.

171
00:12:20,773 --> 00:12:24,410
So why did you stop drawing
halfway through?

172
00:12:27,046 --> 00:12:29,381
For a moment, I was reminded of a moment

173
00:12:29,882 --> 00:12:31,183
in my childhood.

174
00:12:32,885 --> 00:12:35,321
I have a memory of drawing a vivid,

175
00:12:35,888 --> 00:12:39,058
fiery-red sky for a school assignment
or something.

176
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:43,295
Though, come to think of it,
it's probably not a fond memory.

177
00:12:46,065 --> 00:12:47,299
I see.

178
00:12:50,736 --> 00:12:52,505
What were you like as a kid?

179
00:12:55,541 --> 00:12:59,645
I was relatively quiet,
and studied pretty diligently.

180
00:13:00,813 --> 00:13:03,516
My father was big on education,
so he was quite strict.

181
00:13:06,385 --> 00:13:07,887
How is your relationship
with your dad now?

182
00:13:09,421 --> 00:13:12,458
We don't really talk much,
but I'd say it's pretty normal.

183
00:13:13,726 --> 00:13:14,627
I see.

184
00:13:15,127 --> 00:13:16,061
Then I guess it's okay.

185
00:13:16,662 --> 00:13:17,663
What's okay?

186
00:13:18,531 --> 00:13:20,699
- Let's go to your parents' house.
- What?

187
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:22,834
Now?

188
00:13:22,835 --> 00:13:24,436
Put the address in the GPS.

189
00:13:25,004 --> 00:13:26,304
Are you serious?

190
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:28,406
COUNTERTRANSFERENCE

191
00:13:28,407 --> 00:13:29,875
You're studying something?

192
00:13:33,679 --> 00:13:36,714
Umine calls Mr. Tatsuki "Daddy,"

193
00:13:36,715 --> 00:13:40,286
and directs the kind of feelings
one holds for a parent toward him.

194
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:42,520
Yeah.

195
00:13:42,521 --> 00:13:46,158
According to Professor Mikuko,
that's called transference.

196
00:13:47,893 --> 00:13:51,129
And Mr. Tatsuki was also

197
00:13:51,130 --> 00:13:54,200
deeply invested emotionally
when it concerned Umine, right?

198
00:13:55,768 --> 00:13:57,769
Oh, that's called countertransference?

199
00:13:57,770 --> 00:13:58,837
Right.

200
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:02,308
I mean, it doesn't necessarily mean
that it's a bad thing, though.

201
00:14:03,642 --> 00:14:05,044
That's what you're studying?

202
00:14:06,946 --> 00:14:09,647
I was wondering
if there was anything I could do

203
00:14:09,648 --> 00:14:13,385
while Mr. Tatsuki is taking a break.

204
00:14:17,456 --> 00:14:20,993
Oh, speaking of, tomorrow is Umine's
mathematics competition, isn't it?

205
00:14:22,628 --> 00:14:23,996
Yeah.

206
00:14:29,101 --> 00:14:31,971
NATIONAL MATHEMATICS COMPETITION
"THAT'S RIGHT" MOCK EXAM

207
00:14:43,682 --> 00:14:44,683
Come in.

208
00:14:46,185 --> 00:14:49,854
- Hey.
- Tatsuki, what a surprise.

209
00:14:49,855 --> 00:14:52,056
This is Mr. Mikumo from my workplace.

210
00:14:52,057 --> 00:14:53,057
- Hello.
- Hello.

211
00:14:53,058 --> 00:14:55,226
Please come inside.

212
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:56,962
Oh my.

213
00:14:58,697 --> 00:14:59,832
Hey, dear.

214
00:15:03,002 --> 00:15:03,869
What's with that hair?

215
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:05,737
That's my dad.

216
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:07,506
Hello, nice to meet you.

217
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:12,210
I'm Mikumo, the representative
at an alternative school called Yukanai.

218
00:15:12,211 --> 00:15:15,313
- Thank you for helping out my son.
- Not at all.

219
00:15:15,314 --> 00:15:18,284
I really was just passing by,
so I’ll be taking my leave now.

220
00:15:19,251 --> 00:15:20,184
Hold on.

221
00:15:20,185 --> 00:15:22,387
I'll come back to pick you up.
So rest well.

222
00:15:22,388 --> 00:15:25,290
- You've got to be kidding.
- Please stay and eat with us.

223
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:27,425
- Thank you, but please don't mind me.
- Don't leave me.

224
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:28,594
Come over here, dear.

225
00:15:29,695 --> 00:15:31,163
Please stay for a while.

226
00:15:31,897 --> 00:15:33,799
You have to listen to my dad.

227
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:35,833
Fine.

228
00:15:35,834 --> 00:15:38,469
Thank you for your kind offer.

229
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:39,871
Would you like to take a bath?

230
00:15:39,872 --> 00:15:41,507
I'm fine, thank you.

231
00:16:30,889 --> 00:16:34,393
AWARD CERTIFICATE

232
00:16:37,129 --> 00:16:40,365
All right, so what do you think
the protagonist is feeling

233
00:16:40,366 --> 00:16:42,266
- in this scene?
- I know!

234
00:16:42,267 --> 00:16:43,301
Me!

235
00:16:43,302 --> 00:16:44,602
Okay, Koike.

236
00:16:44,603 --> 00:16:46,704
She's feeling sad.

237
00:16:46,705 --> 00:16:48,107
That's correct.

238
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:50,676
Yes, Ukita?

239
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:53,845
Is that really the correct answer?

240
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:55,247
What?

241
00:16:55,814 --> 00:16:57,515
It might not just be sadness.

242
00:16:57,516 --> 00:16:59,250
There might also be feelings of relief.

243
00:16:59,251 --> 00:17:01,586
- But the husband died…
- Or she might be spaced out.

244
00:17:01,587 --> 00:17:04,222
But she lost someone very dear to her…

245
00:17:04,223 --> 00:17:06,457
Is there really only one answer?

246
00:17:06,458 --> 00:17:07,793
That's enough.

247
00:17:16,668 --> 00:17:18,036
For your art homework,

248
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:21,639
please draw a picture
of your favorite type of sky, okay?

249
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,409
Yes.

250
00:17:24,643 --> 00:17:26,011
- I'll draw a whale-shaped cloud.
- Nice.

251
00:17:43,328 --> 00:17:44,930
What are you drawing?

252
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:48,467
It's my homework. I'm drawing the sky.

253
00:17:49,535 --> 00:17:51,770
Why is it red?

254
00:17:57,042 --> 00:17:58,477
That doesn't look like a sky.

255
00:17:59,278 --> 00:18:00,379
Draw it properly.

256
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:02,414
‎What?

257
00:18:03,949 --> 00:18:05,316
Stop messing around,

258
00:18:05,317 --> 00:18:08,554
and draw it properly
so that it actually looks like a sky.

259
00:18:13,058 --> 00:18:13,926
Got it?

260
00:18:16,728 --> 00:18:17,596
Yes.

261
00:18:19,832 --> 00:18:21,466
Ukita's artwork

262
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:25,103
was selected for the city art contest!
Let's hear it for him!

263
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:27,738
- Wow!
- You're amazing!

264
00:18:27,739 --> 00:18:29,041
Come up here, Ukita.

265
00:18:29,908 --> 00:18:32,043
- Yes.
- You're the best!

266
00:18:32,044 --> 00:18:34,078
Congratulations.

267
00:18:34,079 --> 00:18:35,646
Show it to everyone.

268
00:18:35,647 --> 00:18:37,448
Let's give him a round of applause.

269
00:18:37,449 --> 00:18:39,718
Wow!

270
00:18:45,023 --> 00:18:47,593
See? I was right, wasn't I?

271
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:50,194
It really was the right call to redraw it.

272
00:18:50,195 --> 00:18:52,865
You're amazing, Tatsuki.

273
00:19:42,314 --> 00:19:44,550
Which university are you applying for?

274
00:19:48,587 --> 00:19:51,590
After I graduate high school,
I want to study art.

275
00:19:55,394 --> 00:19:57,796
I want to go to a vocational school
specializing in arts.

276
00:19:58,363 --> 00:19:59,898
A vocational school?

277
00:20:05,170 --> 00:20:07,338
What you want to study

278
00:20:07,339 --> 00:20:10,275
is up to you to decide,
so just do whatever you like.

279
00:20:11,276 --> 00:20:14,046
But you have to go to university.

280
00:20:14,746 --> 00:20:15,980
What?

281
00:20:15,981 --> 00:20:18,283
You might not be able
to make a living from art.

282
00:20:19,585 --> 00:20:23,155
Wouldn't going to university
broaden your options?

283
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,392
Is that really so?

284
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:30,095
Go to university.

285
00:20:30,862 --> 00:20:32,698
Your grades aren't bad, after all.

286
00:20:45,310 --> 00:20:47,845
Hey, where's my sketchbook?

287
00:20:47,846 --> 00:20:50,514
It was creating a mess,
so I put it out with the recyclables.

288
00:20:50,515 --> 00:20:52,316
What? Why?

289
00:20:52,317 --> 00:20:56,153
I told you to clean up so many times,
but you never got around to it.

290
00:20:56,154 --> 00:20:58,056
Why did you throw it away?

291
00:20:59,424 --> 00:21:02,393
Don't get so angry with me.

292
00:21:02,394 --> 00:21:03,795
You don't need it for the entrance exams.

293
00:21:12,871 --> 00:21:15,007
This was your room?

294
00:21:16,108 --> 00:21:19,177
Yeah, although it's being used
as a storage room now.

295
00:21:21,013 --> 00:21:22,547
You held on to your work, huh?

296
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:25,083
Look at this.

297
00:21:26,184 --> 00:21:29,921
Dad told me that this doesn't look
like a drawing of the sky.

298
00:21:30,989 --> 00:21:32,357
So I redrew it, and here it is.

299
00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:35,860
I see.

300
00:21:35,861 --> 00:21:39,364
When I did what my dad told me to do,
I ended up winning an award.

301
00:21:40,098 --> 00:21:43,435
From then on, all focus turned
to winning awards.

302
00:21:44,803 --> 00:21:45,704
Even though

303
00:21:46,938 --> 00:21:50,075
I came to love drawing because
it allowed me to express myself freely.

304
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:53,078
I see.

305
00:21:56,148 --> 00:21:58,950
I think the reason why I can't stop
being concerned about Umine

306
00:22:00,719 --> 00:22:03,221
is because her situation
is similar to my own childhood.

307
00:22:04,956 --> 00:22:06,024
I worry

308
00:22:06,792 --> 00:22:09,995
that she's suffering from the pressure
to produce good results.

309
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:14,166
You might be right.

310
00:22:20,138 --> 00:22:22,140
I wonder what kind of feelings

311
00:22:23,575 --> 00:22:25,877
you dad had toward you back then.

312
00:22:26,445 --> 00:22:29,414
My dad's feelings?

313
00:22:34,853 --> 00:22:36,655
Is Sora doing well?

314
00:22:44,863 --> 00:22:45,964
You still see him?

315
00:22:46,732 --> 00:22:47,765
I saw him recently.

316
00:22:47,766 --> 00:22:48,934
I see.

317
00:22:50,202 --> 00:22:52,804
We were worried about
how things have been since the divorce.

318
00:23:09,588 --> 00:23:11,490
You fish?

319
00:23:12,124 --> 00:23:13,859
Yeah, you didn't know?

320
00:23:14,993 --> 00:23:16,294
I never saw him fishing.

321
00:23:17,829 --> 00:23:19,864
Well, he was always buried in work.

322
00:23:19,865 --> 00:23:21,199
But now he has the time.

323
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:22,834
Wanna go together?

324
00:23:24,035 --> 00:23:26,905
No, thanks.

325
00:23:27,973 --> 00:23:29,207
It's fun.

326
00:23:32,043 --> 00:23:33,745
Go take a bath.

327
00:23:36,448 --> 00:23:37,282
Okay.

328
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:44,322
I didn't know that fishing was your hobby.

329
00:23:47,025 --> 00:23:48,326
I started after I retired.

330
00:23:50,762 --> 00:23:53,432
I thought you weren't the type
who could sit still like this.

331
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:57,536
Yeah, now that you mention it.

332
00:23:58,537 --> 00:23:59,671
I guess you changed.

333
00:24:01,540 --> 00:24:02,574
Probably.

334
00:24:08,547 --> 00:24:10,015
When I was a kid

335
00:24:12,184 --> 00:24:15,654
I won an award
for drawing a picture of a blue sky.

336
00:24:16,822 --> 00:24:17,756
Do you remember?

337
00:24:19,991 --> 00:24:21,693
A drawing of a blue sky?

338
00:24:22,694 --> 00:24:25,597
I don't remember.

339
00:24:29,201 --> 00:24:30,202
I figured.

340
00:24:31,970 --> 00:24:34,673
But I remember you were good at drawing.

341
00:24:38,944 --> 00:24:41,313
Why do you bring that up?

342
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:52,991
At first, I had drawn a red sky,

343
00:24:53,992 --> 00:24:55,560
but I was forced to redraw it.

344
00:24:56,428 --> 00:24:57,295
By whom?

345
00:24:58,163 --> 00:24:59,231
You.

346
00:25:00,632 --> 00:25:01,466
Why would I do that?

347
00:25:02,267 --> 00:25:05,937
You said that a red sky was unrealistic
and told me to redraw a blue sky.

348
00:25:06,938 --> 00:25:09,074
- I said that?
- Yes, you, Dad.

349
00:25:12,777 --> 00:25:14,379
You don't remember it at all?

350
00:25:16,214 --> 00:25:19,818
I mean, a red sky would've been just fine.

351
00:25:20,552 --> 00:25:21,952
Right?

352
00:25:21,953 --> 00:25:23,387
That always bothered me.

353
00:25:23,388 --> 00:25:25,257
I always wondered
why the sky had to be blue.

354
00:25:26,057 --> 00:25:26,892
Yeah, why is that?

355
00:25:27,659 --> 00:25:28,960
That's what I want to know!

356
00:25:30,495 --> 00:25:33,797
You should have just done
whatever you wanted.

357
00:25:33,798 --> 00:25:36,067
That wasn't the vibe at all back then.

358
00:25:36,568 --> 00:25:37,469
Not at all.

359
00:25:43,441 --> 00:25:45,143
I see…

360
00:25:51,516 --> 00:25:53,218
I guess your mom and I

361
00:25:54,352 --> 00:25:57,355
were just desperate to keep you
from straying off the path

362
00:25:58,056 --> 00:26:02,494
and to prevent you from failing.

363
00:26:06,798 --> 00:26:09,701
Are you still holding a grudge
against me for that?

364
00:26:12,737 --> 00:26:13,572
No.

365
00:26:17,676 --> 00:26:21,146
You guys put me through university,
and I was able to find a job.

366
00:26:22,247 --> 00:26:23,548
A lot happened since then,

367
00:26:24,983 --> 00:26:26,251
but it led me to where I am now.

368
00:26:28,186 --> 00:26:29,187
I'm glad.

369
00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:32,257
But

370
00:26:34,726 --> 00:26:37,629
I did to Sora the exact same thing
you did to me.

371
00:26:39,230 --> 00:26:40,365
‎What?

372
00:26:44,202 --> 00:26:46,037
To ensure he wouldn't stray from the path

373
00:26:48,340 --> 00:26:49,708
<i>and to prevent him from failing,</i>

374
00:26:52,677 --> 00:26:54,279
<i>I forced my own values upon him…</i>

375
00:26:58,550 --> 00:26:59,851
and drove Sora into a corner.

376
00:27:03,555 --> 00:27:04,489
That's

377
00:27:05,724 --> 00:27:07,125
not good.

378
00:27:14,733 --> 00:27:16,501
Although I don't want to
hear that from you.

379
00:27:20,939 --> 00:27:22,574
Was I really

380
00:27:23,808 --> 00:27:26,311
- that kind of a parent?
- Huh?

381
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:32,883
Was I really the type
to micromanage your life?

382
00:27:32,884 --> 00:27:35,220
Yes, I never had a say in anything.

383
00:27:39,457 --> 00:27:41,025
Is that right?

384
00:27:41,026 --> 00:27:42,594
Yeah.

385
00:27:44,162 --> 00:27:46,563
I have no recollection of that at all.

386
00:27:46,564 --> 00:27:48,366
You better not forget it anymore.

387
00:27:52,537 --> 00:27:56,908
NATIONAL MATHEMATICS COMPETITION

388
00:27:58,443 --> 00:27:59,678
I'll go in now.

389
00:28:00,779 --> 00:28:03,014
Don't rush, and stay calm.

390
00:28:08,253 --> 00:28:10,522
Go get the gold medal.

391
00:28:24,069 --> 00:28:25,136
I'll do my best.

392
00:28:33,778 --> 00:28:37,382
I wonder how Umine is doing
at her mathematics competition.

393
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:39,584
Yeah, I wonder.

394
00:28:40,752 --> 00:28:43,555
I want her to do her best, but…

395
00:28:44,122 --> 00:28:45,789
Yeah.

396
00:28:45,790 --> 00:28:47,625
I wonder if she'll be back
starting tomorrow.

397
00:28:48,727 --> 00:28:50,227
I hope so.

398
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:54,098
I hope she doesn't end up
clinging on to Tatsuki again.

399
00:28:54,099 --> 00:28:56,834
Apparently,
one way to prevent that from happening

400
00:28:56,835 --> 00:29:00,271
is to distribute the interactions
she has with people.

401
00:29:00,972 --> 00:29:02,207
Distribute?

402
00:29:02,707 --> 00:29:05,709
It's important to reduce the time
she spends alone with Mr. Tatsuki,

403
00:29:05,710 --> 00:29:08,680
and all of us need to start
interacting with her as well.

404
00:29:10,882 --> 00:29:14,685
The idea is to "spread out
and diversify the support system."

405
00:29:14,686 --> 00:29:18,422
So, basically, all of us should
rally around Umine.

406
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:19,556
That's right.

407
00:29:19,557 --> 00:29:22,926
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

408
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:25,130
What are we doing for
the graduation party performance?

409
00:29:26,197 --> 00:29:28,966
We haven't talked to you guys about it.
What do you want to do?

410
00:29:28,967 --> 00:29:30,467
I want to put on a puppet show.

411
00:29:30,468 --> 00:29:32,604
- That's a good idea.
- Yeah.

412
00:29:33,271 --> 00:29:34,972
Can we join you guys too?

413
00:29:34,973 --> 00:29:36,374
- Yeah.
- Of course.

414
00:29:37,142 --> 00:29:38,675
Shi-chan and Ajicchan,

415
00:29:38,676 --> 00:29:41,345
- you guys can borrow my stuffed toys.
- Thank you.

416
00:29:41,346 --> 00:29:43,248
Do I get to play a role too?

417
00:29:44,449 --> 00:29:45,415
Let's see…

418
00:29:45,416 --> 00:29:48,086
- You can be Muscle Man.
- Muscle Man!

419
00:29:49,654 --> 00:29:51,623
I won't be using a doll then?

420
00:29:52,157 --> 00:29:52,991
Just your arms.

421
00:30:01,666 --> 00:30:03,334
Were you able to talk with your dad?

422
00:30:03,902 --> 00:30:04,769
Yes.

423
00:30:05,270 --> 00:30:06,571
<i>How did it go?</i>

424
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:08,239
It turns out

425
00:30:09,474 --> 00:30:12,209
he doesn't remember any of that stuff
he did in the past at all.

426
00:30:12,210 --> 00:30:14,078
He was so unbothered by it,
it was anticlimactic.

427
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:17,248
That's awesome.

428
00:30:18,149 --> 00:30:19,617
It's not funny.

429
00:30:21,219 --> 00:30:23,955
I guess it just goes to show that
even parents aren't perfect.

430
00:30:24,956 --> 00:30:26,090
Yeah.

431
00:30:28,526 --> 00:30:31,196
I gave a lot of thought regarding

432
00:30:32,330 --> 00:30:33,798
Umine and Sora.

433
00:30:35,233 --> 00:30:36,134
<i>Is that right?</i>

434
00:30:37,435 --> 00:30:40,138
There's something I want to tell Umine.

435
00:30:43,641 --> 00:30:45,210
Is it okay if I return to Yukanai?

436
00:30:47,445 --> 00:30:48,713
Okay.

437
00:30:49,948 --> 00:30:50,782
I'll pick you up.

438
00:30:52,584 --> 00:30:53,885
Thank you.

439
00:31:03,928 --> 00:31:05,262
- Okay.
- That's good.

440
00:31:05,263 --> 00:31:06,964
- Where to next?
- Right.

441
00:31:06,965 --> 00:31:08,800
- Right?
- No, left.

442
00:31:12,904 --> 00:31:14,172
Hello.

443
00:31:16,741 --> 00:31:18,710
Long time no see, Umine.

444
00:31:19,210 --> 00:31:20,645
It's been a while, Shi-chan.

445
00:31:21,145 --> 00:31:22,846
It's been a while.

446
00:31:22,847 --> 00:31:24,282
What do you want to do?

447
00:31:24,782 --> 00:31:26,950
Want to make <i>takoyaki</i>? Or popcorn?

448
00:31:26,951 --> 00:31:29,587
Let's do whatever you feel like.

449
00:31:44,602 --> 00:31:47,137
- Hey everyone, we're back.
- We're back.

450
00:31:47,138 --> 00:31:48,572
It's Tatsuki!

451
00:31:48,573 --> 00:31:50,207
- Tatsuki, you're back!
- Welcome back.

452
00:31:50,208 --> 00:31:52,042
- You're okay now?
- Yup.

453
00:31:52,043 --> 00:31:53,011
Did you bring gifts?

454
00:31:53,878 --> 00:31:55,013
Sorry, I don't have any.

455
00:31:55,580 --> 00:31:56,781
That's too bad.

456
00:31:58,983 --> 00:32:00,218
Welcome back.

457
00:32:00,718 --> 00:32:01,919
Thanks for all your help.

458
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:02,987
It was no problem.

459
00:32:03,821 --> 00:32:05,156
Umine is here.

460
00:32:06,591 --> 00:32:08,191
Look at this.

461
00:32:08,192 --> 00:32:10,060
AWARD CERTIFICATE
MISS UMINE ANDO

462
00:32:10,061 --> 00:32:11,062
I got third place.

463
00:32:12,130 --> 00:32:13,831
You won third place? Congratulations!

464
00:32:14,899 --> 00:32:16,701
I ran out of time
and messed up at the end.

465
00:32:17,468 --> 00:32:19,002
She tried,

466
00:32:19,003 --> 00:32:20,438
but she fell just short of the goal.

467
00:32:21,472 --> 00:32:23,508
Winning a bronze medal is an amazing feat.

468
00:32:24,709 --> 00:32:26,244
Oh, I guess so.

469
00:32:28,112 --> 00:32:29,981
Hey everyone, attention please!

470
00:32:30,648 --> 00:32:31,615
What is it?

471
00:32:31,616 --> 00:32:34,084
We're going to do button art now!

472
00:32:34,085 --> 00:32:36,353
Wow, look at all those buttons.

473
00:32:36,354 --> 00:32:39,524
There are plenty of buttons,
so feel free to use as many as you like.

474
00:32:41,426 --> 00:32:43,894
Umine, want to try button art again?

475
00:32:43,895 --> 00:32:46,264
- Yeah.
- Okay.

476
00:32:47,065 --> 00:32:49,833
All right, go ahead
and use the buttons however you like

477
00:32:49,834 --> 00:32:51,034
to express whatever you want!

478
00:32:51,035 --> 00:32:53,071
Okay!

479
00:32:58,576 --> 00:32:59,410
This is crazy.

480
00:33:01,079 --> 00:33:02,480
What should I make?

481
00:33:08,686 --> 00:33:11,889
What do you like, Umine?

482
00:33:16,627 --> 00:33:17,462
Math?

483
00:33:21,399 --> 00:33:22,467
Right now

484
00:33:24,836 --> 00:33:26,337
I don't like it that much.

485
00:33:34,712 --> 00:33:38,116
What did you like about math?

486
00:33:49,093 --> 00:33:50,094
When I was little,

487
00:33:51,529 --> 00:33:55,666
around your age, I loved to draw.

488
00:33:57,068 --> 00:33:58,202
That was because

489
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:02,874
it allowed me to express myself freely.

490
00:34:11,682 --> 00:34:13,618
I wonder why I fell in love with math?

491
00:35:22,186 --> 00:35:25,022
Now that you’ve finished making it,
how do you feel?

492
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:30,895
When doing math

493
00:35:33,931 --> 00:35:36,467
I liked getting
the flashes of inspiration.

494
00:35:41,339 --> 00:35:43,474
That's what made me fall in love with it.

495
00:35:46,244 --> 00:35:47,311
I see.

496
00:35:53,317 --> 00:35:54,852
But I wonder why…

497
00:36:04,495 --> 00:36:06,597
I wonder why I stopped loving it.

498
00:36:21,913 --> 00:36:23,346
All right everyone,

499
00:36:23,347 --> 00:36:25,683
you can display your artwork
wherever you like.

500
00:36:26,250 --> 00:36:27,518
Okay.

501
00:36:28,019 --> 00:36:30,320
Let's display ours together.

502
00:36:30,321 --> 00:36:32,757
- You can display it wherever you want.
- Umine!

503
00:36:33,824 --> 00:36:35,659
Do you want to join our puppet show

504
00:36:35,660 --> 00:36:37,128
at the graduation party?

505
00:36:38,663 --> 00:36:41,866
You haven't been able to play at all
because of the math competition, right?

506
00:36:47,605 --> 00:36:48,806
Here.

507
00:36:51,209 --> 00:36:52,910
She wants to give it back to you.

508
00:36:56,147 --> 00:36:59,483
You're a big girl now,
so you don't need this, right?

509
00:37:03,888 --> 00:37:04,755
I…

510
00:37:06,357 --> 00:37:07,625
sold this already.

511
00:37:08,626 --> 00:37:10,228
But it's yours, Umine.

512
00:37:26,110 --> 00:37:27,010
MIDDLE SCHOOL GRADUATION PARTY

513
00:37:27,011 --> 00:37:31,314
<i>See you again, see you again</i>

514
00:37:31,315 --> 00:37:34,785
<i>No need to feel lonely anymore</i>

515
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:39,889
<i>I'll always be here waiting for you</i>

516
00:37:39,890 --> 00:37:44,262
<i>It's okay, you can do it</i>

517
00:37:48,532 --> 00:37:49,432
All right,

518
00:37:49,433 --> 00:37:51,769
let's begin
the middle school graduation party.

519
00:37:54,839 --> 00:37:56,406
To kick things off,

520
00:37:56,407 --> 00:37:59,110
let's hear from the two students
graduating from middle school this year.

521
00:37:59,677 --> 00:38:01,745
Let's hear it for Takumi.

522
00:38:01,746 --> 00:38:03,213
Hey.

523
00:38:03,214 --> 00:38:04,882
I'm Tonetaku,
Yukanai's charismatic figure!

524
00:38:06,050 --> 00:38:06,950
That's hilarious.

525
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:08,351
Who said you're charismatic?

526
00:38:08,352 --> 00:38:09,787
Please keep it short.

527
00:38:11,389 --> 00:38:14,692
I didn't attend middle school at all,

528
00:38:15,459 --> 00:38:17,795
so Yukanai is what I consider
my middle school.

529
00:38:18,996 --> 00:38:22,300
The precious time I spent here
with everyone

530
00:38:23,834 --> 00:38:25,903
was very…

531
00:38:27,104 --> 00:38:28,539
How should I say it…?

532
00:38:29,540 --> 00:38:31,342
- You're crying?
- Is he okay?

533
00:38:31,909 --> 00:38:34,077
- He's really crying?
- Really?

534
00:38:34,078 --> 00:38:35,246
Psyche!

535
00:38:36,814 --> 00:38:38,049
You totally got me.

536
00:38:39,483 --> 00:38:41,217
Sorry, guys.

537
00:38:41,218 --> 00:38:43,119
Let's continue being friends from now on.

538
00:38:43,120 --> 00:38:44,688
I love all of you.

539
00:38:44,689 --> 00:38:46,122
- Give me a high-five.
- Okay.

540
00:38:46,123 --> 00:38:47,090
Yeah!

541
00:38:47,091 --> 00:38:48,491
Thank you.

542
00:38:48,492 --> 00:38:50,728
Next up is Tomoki.

543
00:38:57,668 --> 00:38:58,569
If…

544
00:39:00,304 --> 00:39:02,807
I hadn't met Tatsuki and Shi-chan,

545
00:39:03,708 --> 00:39:06,143
I might not even be alive right now.

546
00:39:08,546 --> 00:39:10,047
So I'm very grateful.

547
00:39:12,216 --> 00:39:13,184
Thank you.

548
00:39:15,786 --> 00:39:17,253
You're going to make me cry.

549
00:39:17,254 --> 00:39:19,923
- Thank you, Tomoki!
- You're so cool, Tomoki.

550
00:39:19,924 --> 00:39:21,359
Someday,

551
00:39:21,859 --> 00:39:24,328
I’m going to become
the world’s number one esports player,

552
00:39:24,929 --> 00:39:26,831
become filthy rich,

553
00:39:27,398 --> 00:39:28,933
and blow everyone’s minds!

554
00:39:32,970 --> 00:39:33,903
That's awesome.

555
00:39:33,904 --> 00:39:36,906
Well, even after they graduate
middle school,

556
00:39:36,907 --> 00:39:39,342
they can drop by Yukanai
whenever they want,

557
00:39:39,343 --> 00:39:40,778
so let's all hang out again!

558
00:39:44,882 --> 00:39:46,850
And now, onto the puppet show

559
00:39:46,851 --> 00:39:49,820
"The Adventures
of the Witches Riri and Ruru."

560
00:39:50,388 --> 00:39:51,821
Ready?

561
00:39:51,822 --> 00:39:53,858
Let's begin!

562
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:01,231
If you want to go any further,

563
00:40:01,232 --> 00:40:04,402
you must solve the question
I'm going to give you.

564
00:40:05,669 --> 00:40:08,272
Oh no! Everyone, help us figure it out.

565
00:40:09,340 --> 00:40:11,574
Okay, let's begin.

566
00:40:11,575 --> 00:40:13,676
A notebook and an eraser

567
00:40:13,677 --> 00:40:15,979
cost 110 yen altogether.

568
00:40:15,980 --> 00:40:19,516
The notebook is 100 yen more expensive
than the eraser.

569
00:40:19,517 --> 00:40:20,717
Then

570
00:40:20,718 --> 00:40:23,887
how much does the eraser cost?

571
00:40:23,888 --> 00:40:25,622
- Isn't it ten yen?
- Yeah, ten yen.

572
00:40:25,623 --> 00:40:27,791
- Oh yeah?
- It's really ten yen?

573
00:40:27,792 --> 00:40:30,627
- Yeah, it's ten yen.
- Ten yen.

574
00:40:30,628 --> 00:40:33,329
It's gotta be ten yen, right?

575
00:40:33,330 --> 00:40:34,497
I got it!

576
00:40:34,498 --> 00:40:36,700
- Your answer please!
- Five yen.

577
00:40:37,401 --> 00:40:40,037
- Correct!
- Hooray!

578
00:40:53,317 --> 00:40:55,486
It’s been a long time since I’ve seen her

579
00:40:56,821 --> 00:40:58,289
look so happy.

580
00:41:00,891 --> 00:41:01,725
Yeah.

581
00:41:04,361 --> 00:41:06,563
The bridge opened up.

582
00:41:06,564 --> 00:41:07,665
In the beginning,

583
00:41:09,400 --> 00:41:11,634
whenever she was able to solve
a math problem,

584
00:41:11,635 --> 00:41:14,038
she had the look of pure joy.

585
00:41:15,739 --> 00:41:17,774
- I solved it.
- Correct.

586
00:41:17,775 --> 00:41:19,743
All right!

587
00:41:23,380 --> 00:41:25,316
<i>That made me really happy too.</i>

588
00:41:27,051 --> 00:41:28,219
And I wanted

589
00:41:29,353 --> 00:41:30,988
to give her even more reasons to smile.

590
00:41:32,923 --> 00:41:34,892
What kind of a country are we in?

591
00:41:35,459 --> 00:41:37,760
It is a country that cherishes

592
00:41:37,761 --> 00:41:39,997
the things that you love.

593
00:41:41,398 --> 00:41:43,067
The things that I love…

594
00:41:44,935 --> 00:41:47,238
But somewhere along the way,

595
00:41:49,406 --> 00:41:52,276
mathematics turned into
something painful for Umine.

596
00:42:00,818 --> 00:42:02,319
I took away

597
00:42:04,421 --> 00:42:05,523
something precious

598
00:42:07,691 --> 00:42:09,593
that Umine loved.

599
00:42:21,071 --> 00:42:22,006
Mr. Ando.

600
00:42:26,911 --> 00:42:28,445
You and Umine

601
00:42:30,915 --> 00:42:32,316
will be just fine.

602
00:42:38,188 --> 00:42:40,758
Ruru, what do you want to do
in this country?

603
00:42:41,392 --> 00:42:42,726
I'll think a lot.

604
00:42:43,961 --> 00:42:46,163
- I'll play a lot.
- That's nice.

605
00:42:47,565 --> 00:42:48,399
And

606
00:42:49,066 --> 00:42:50,568
I'll wait for flashes of inspiration.

607
00:42:51,802 --> 00:42:53,469
That's awesome.

608
00:42:53,470 --> 00:42:55,172
How lovely.

609
00:42:55,673 --> 00:42:56,906
That's the end of

610
00:42:56,907 --> 00:43:01,045
"The Adventures
of the Witches Riri and Ruru."

611
00:43:02,079 --> 00:43:03,613
Ready?

612
00:43:03,614 --> 00:43:06,750
Thank you very much.

613
00:43:08,452 --> 00:43:09,954
Thank you.

614
00:43:25,970 --> 00:43:27,003
Thank you.

615
00:43:27,004 --> 00:43:28,105
Not at all.

616
00:43:31,241 --> 00:43:32,943
I want to do some math quizzes
when I get home!

617
00:43:36,914 --> 00:43:37,748
Okay, let's do it.

618
00:43:42,486 --> 00:43:44,088
Bye, Tatsuki.

619
00:43:46,390 --> 00:43:48,525
Until next time, Umine.

620
00:43:52,329 --> 00:43:53,564
Let's go, Daddy.

621
00:43:59,503 --> 00:44:01,639
All right, shall we clean up?

622
00:44:02,139 --> 00:44:03,207
Yeah.

623
00:44:18,355 --> 00:44:19,356
YU
13 MISSED CALLS

624
00:44:21,525 --> 00:44:22,526
YU

625
00:44:33,937 --> 00:44:34,805
Please, stop.

626
00:44:37,241 --> 00:44:38,509
Stop this, Sora.

627
00:44:47,317 --> 00:44:48,752
- What the hell, damn it!
- Sora!

628
00:44:53,557 --> 00:44:54,491
Hey.

629
00:44:56,126 --> 00:44:57,127
What are you doing?

630
00:45:01,865 --> 00:45:03,167
Shut up!

631
00:45:07,971 --> 00:45:09,906
I wonder where we went wrong.

632
00:45:09,907 --> 00:45:11,107
THIS DRAMA IS FICTIONAL

633
00:45:11,108 --> 00:45:14,445
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
